On a recommendation from a local, my partner and I made reservations at The Helmand, located in Mt. Vernon, near downtown Baltimore.  The restaurant boasts authentic Afghani cuisine, and has been open for 25 years.  We were lucky to find street parking steps away from the front door on such a cold night.  Short of having us sit on the floor, the restaurant had an authentic Middle-Eastern feel.  Two dining areas were set with white table linens and cloth napkins.  Although the tables seemed too wide for intimate conversation, the staff was amenable to a seating adjustment.  The star of the show was the food.  We started with the kaddo borawani, an appetizer of pan-fried baby pumpkin seasoned with sugar and yogurt garlic sauce.  This dish was surprisingly tasty, and not too sweet.  We complemented this with a Spanish red wine and a large order of Naan.  The small order of Naan would have sufficed for two.  If you are familiar with traditional Indian naan, heads up.  This naan is heartier, slightly thicker, and seasoned perfectly.  The wine list included mostly California, French, Italian and Spanish wines.  Many options were by the bottle only, but there were plenty of choices by the glass as well.  We shared a main dish, the zardalu challow.  Tender pieces of lamb seasoned with apricot, tomatoes, garlic, turmeric, and chili peppers were served with sweet, spicy turnips and challow (specially prepared long-grain rice). An interesting sauce of cilantro and lime was brought to add to the challow.  The sweet and spicy flavors of this dish were intense, and paired well with the Spanish wine.  I’m not used to eating food with so much flavor; this is where The Helmand shines.  After finishing the entre, we ordered two desserts and coffee; we were pleased to discover The Helmand serves authentic Turkish coffee.  The feereny was a light custard topped with fresh fruit.  It was overshadowed by the Afghani ice cream, however.  Listed on the menu as “special ice cream,” the cardamom-infused vanilla ice cream is served on top of dates, figs, and mangoes.  Definitely our favorite.  Service at The Helmand was timely, but curt.  There was no engagement with the wait-staff; they did their job efficiently, and did not interrupt our meal or conversation.  This felt like their style.  Main dishes range from $14 to $20, with a few choices above that range (rack of lamb, for example).   The prices felt reasonable for quality food, authentic atmosphere, and prompt service.  With tip expect to pay about $50 per person, which would include one appetizer, naan, two glasses wine, two entrees, two coffees, and two desserts.  We recommend The Helmand for date-night, special occasions, or just because you haven’t tried Afghani food yet.

Good food that fell just a little short of being perfect. I had the pumpkin appetizer "Kaddo Borwani" which was very unique. The pumpkin was quite sweet but not overdone and we'll cooked. Soft but not mushy. The garlic yogurt sauce on top is subtle but an interesting savory component that you might not expect from pumpkin.  I got the lamb lawand for an appetizer and this was definitely the highlight of the night with four components plated separately. The rice was well seasoned and quite delicious but there were some crunchy overcooked bits that I could have done without. The lime mint sauce was fantastic and amazing. The lamb stew with mushrooms was quite nice. The spinach side "sabzy" was well cooked but the flavor profile wasn't quite what I liked so used the lamb sauce to complement it.  The special ice cream dessert with cardamom and dates, mangoes was not as impressive as some reviewers pointed out and I would personally skip that.  Finally the staff were extremely busy but the water refills were extremely prompt and dirty dishes did not sit around on the table for long. Ordering however was quite delayed and could have been more prompt. Overall decor is nice albeit extremely dim.

Loved the food. I don't know a lot about Afghanistan cuisine but I know when food is superb. Traditional dishes were served in savory sauces, seasoned perfectly. Plenty of vegetarian options and a good wine list. Bonus is that it's not too pricey at all. It was packed when I went on a Monday night and every time I pass The Helmand on my way home it's always busy.
A bit on the expensive side but pretty good food. They had a surprisingly large number of vegetarian options too!
Everything the chef cooks is just completely sublime! I've never left there feeling anything but totally satisfied and content.
Great food.  Have been with a group of 13 and the Chef made super recommendation.  All of us have been impressed  of quality and taste of food.
Amazing food! The sweet spicy turnips are incredible, the lamb/beef meatballs and especially the Zardalu Challow are the bomb! The special ice cream is awesome!

The food is fantastic here. It was my first time trying Afghani food, although I love Indian and Mediterranean cuisine. Environment is intimate  and wonderful for small and large parties alike. Be prepared to use your phone flashlight to read the menu though. Its very dimly lit.
This is a favorite of mine in Baltimore. The food never disappoints. The service feels rushed, but I didn't come to make friends with the wait staff, right?
Delicious food!! Great service! Definitely coming back
Vegetarian options are not great
Authentic Afghan dishes to satisfy the adventurous

The Helmand is one of our favorite places. We drive an hour to eat here for special occasions or when we're nearby. Every dish is extraordinary, even the bread! Don't miss the appetizers or the desserts for the complete experience.
Superb. Great place for a date.
Get the pumpkin and the vegetarian aushak and be happy

The food was okay and the service was fast. We came for a birthday celebration but since the last time we were here the tables seemed smaller and crowded closer together. The dinner plates and serving dishes had to be constantly shifted to access the water glasses. The noise level was so high it was difficult to have a conversation at our table and we left immediately after the meal, skipping dessert. The lights were so dim that we and people at other tables were using their cell phones to read the menu. The cell phone at the table next to use was shining directly  in our guest face while the person holding the phone was oblivious for nearly 5 minutes.
One of the finest restaurants in Baltimore, I ALWAYS feel like a VIP when I dine here.

New in town and searched for a good restaurant, my first experience there I went on a friday and no one was at the front to attend me, I walked to the back and asked an employee(white older lady) if there was any tables available she gave me an attitude and said I'd have to wait, I stood in the back waiting for about 25 min and decided it was Too packed to wait and ate at another similiar restaurant across the street, I really wanted to test the food there and decided to go the next day early at 5pm to make sure they can't say no or tell me to wait. I was the first one there and enjoyed the food(server never brought out my drink and I had to remind her after I finished the meal) and ended up ordering another order to take home. From my first experience I figure let me start reserving online so there's no inconvenience when I get there. I reserved for 7pm and get there at 6:55pm, I get told to wait at the back. 8pm hits and I noticed two different couples just coming in the door were attended and put on tables just coming through the doors. After waiting for over an hour and seeing this happend made me feel some type of way(self explanatory)and again left to another restaurant for the 2nd time. I intended to  be a regular customer and buy two meals every time I would go there and show this business support. However after this experience, I don't think I will ever go there again.

Consistently one of the best restaurants in the Baltimore/DC area. Been dozens of times over the years and have tried almost everything on the menu. Not a single dish I wouldn't get again. Classics include the baby pumpkin appetizer and beef tenderloin dinner. Chicken lawland is excellent as well. One of a kind experience that cannot be found anywhere else. Must try!
Really great lamb and wide selection of wine
One of the best restaurants in Baltimore. The food is awesome. Great service. Good location. Make sure you try their signature pumpkin appetizer!

My wife and I had reservations at a different, newer, trendy, popular place that fell through because their host staff was... inhospitable. The Helmand was a last minute replacement and we were both blown away by their friendly, knowledgeable staff and even more so by the amazing food.  The dishes we had were all fantastic, but the one that stuck out the most was a roast pumpkin with a garlic yogurt sauce appetizer that we both could have easily had a quadruple order of each for appetizer, entree, and dessert.  Its THAT good!  Their wine selection is decent, the location is good with ample parking in a lot just down the block.  The only caveat is that the seating is close together so don't go thinking you'll get a quiet spot with your date.  Expect to talk with other guests and ogle each others meals.
The pumpkin with garlic yogurt sauce is amazing, and we had a wonderful waitress!

Equisite cuisine sophisticatedly combining delightful textures and flavors. An elegant atmosphere with Afghan decor and top-notch service. One of the loveliest dining experiences I've had in my lifetime!
The chicken kabob was divine. The naan bread is the best ever!!
Great variety of vegetarian dishes!
Always satisfying
The Lamb Here Is awesome
Kabuki was delicious. A large portion, big enough to split. Good service.

My favorite restaurant in Baltimore. I’ve always had excellent meals and consistently stellar service. Exotic, flavorful, but not spicy hot. Fine dining that’s not overdone. A perfect place for a date or a group of friends.
This is a great (double) date place.  The food is great, the atmosphere is exciting, and yet you can hear everyone at your table.

The Helmand is one Baltimore establishment that you do not want to miss.  My then boyfriend, now husband and I first went here for Valentine's Day a couple of years ago and the only reservation I could get was at 9PM that night. We had no idea what to expect, and were absolutely blown away. Incredible atmosphere, food, and service. Even though it was busy everything came out timely and delicious. We have since gone one other time and unfortunately now live in another state but when we're in Baltimore The Helmand is a MUST. Admittedly I dream about it while eating other food because dining there is heavenly. The pumpkin with yogurt sauce appetizer is mind blowing. And don't skip on dessert and go for the cardamom ice cream with dates, apricots, and the likes.
Nice place, nice atmosphere, vegetarian options available, average food
The BREAD! The Smell of BREAD!
So delicious! Everything was perfect. Plenty of vegan options and a great atmosphere.

The food here is completely incredible! The service was amazingly fast and very friendly! I was pleased with the reasonable pricing and the variety of the menu. I wanted to try it all! I would highly recommend the Aushak entree! Can’t wait to go back.

This Baltimore favorite features Afghan cuisine in an upscale yet casual setting. The food is spectacular and the service impeccable. The owner is very engaged in his hospitality and he is ever-present making sure guests are enjoying themselves. The decor includes artworks from the region and a beautiful traditional costume. Prices are very, very fair for a restaurant of this calibre. Entrees running in the $17-$18 range and capping out in the mid-$20 for steak entree (that's just delectable.) One of our diners has a sensitivity to onions and garlic and the owner and chef did blackflips to accommodate her. Truly wonderful restaurant.
Great atmosphere, great service and most important the food was on time and on point
A great experience overall.  After we were seated that is. We had reservations and still had to wait to be seated.  Food is good.
Highly recommended.   Everything was fresh and flavorful!  First dining experience of Afgani food and loved it.
Top notch dining experience. Great service, presentation and atmosphere.
Good food and service
Love this place.  Special ice cream is always a treat!

It was simply great. I had a three course meal with wine and Turkish coffee. The service was good and we were seated quickly. The food was succulent and aromatic. The staff were friendly. I would go again anyday.

Every time I visit Baltimore I go back to the Helmand. For apps, make sure to try the pumpkin with garlic yogurt and the Mantwo (a delicious meat dumpling with sauce). My favorite entree is the Lamb Lawand but I've never had something here I didn't enjoy.
The food here is so good and all of the staff are very friendly.
Great atmosphere wonderful food and it's also a family place
Great place, a bit pricey but food is delicious.
Very delicious food but the customer service SUCKS!

One of my favorites. The Helmand has been a consistently wonderful restaurant for years now. And it was, again, my last visit. The Afghan cuisine is a great split from usual fare - and always prepared/cooked well.  My previous visit was an Artscape (Bmore's yearly "arts" fest) night (and rain to boot, driving a number of people without reservations), so  a little more crowded, a little more noisy, slightly less attentive service (forgiven). Reservations advised. For the dollar, you cannot beat this place.
We always love the Helmand. Most dishes are gluten free and everything is packed with flavor. I can get a bit loud with all the conversations around you however.
Absolutely delicious food, lovely atmosphere, nice staff, easy parking
Afghan dishes to die for. Friendly service. Best lamb of anywhere I have eaten. Can't get there often enough!
Food was OK  but very poor service.. menu is very limited..only 6 main course entrees with a few appetizer options. Doesn't really feel like a afghan place, more like a western cuisine.
Great food.  Ordered a second meal to take home. Wish it was closer to me.
Start with the pumpkin. End with a cafe.

(Translated by Google) Very terrible frankness and sophistication and the service deserves more than five stars 0550490404  (Original) رهيب جدا بصراحه وراقي والخدمه مميزه يستحق اكثر من خمس نجوم ٠٥٥٠٤٩٠٤٠٤
Receptive service, strong atmosphere, and quality Afghan food. Excited to return.

Service was great and very attentive. We went on a fairly busy Friday night; made reservations so didn't have to wait long. The food was just okay. The lamb was incredibly tough and the naan almost completely flavorless. The appetizers were the high point of the meal.
Delicious and inexpensive. Busy most nights, though there has never been a wait time.
Supremely delicious, interesting and well presented.
Great surprise this Afghan restaurant in Baltimore. Delicious and great service
Nice food nice service
Excellent!
Impressive. First time in an Afgan restaurant, and I loved it. We chose the tasting menu and tried so many delicious dishes... Will be back soon! Thank you for the dinner and the nice service!!

If you're looking for hearty comfort with a flair for something different while being somewhat familiar (think Persian or Levantine), then definitely check out this Afghani Mt Vernon mainstay. Anything with the turnips as a side dish or plating piece is worth it, for the root vegetables themselves are par excellence.
One of my favorite Baltimore restaurant.  The pumpkin appraiser knocks your socks off!  Can’t go wrong w the fresh bread and lamb dishes.  Not a big fan of their desserts.

Staff is very friendly. The food is good. It's almost like Indian food, but a little different. I had the stuffed peppers. Can't remember the Afghan name. My company had veggie platter and that was nice. We had the special Afghan ice cream and that was fantastic.
We had a great time at the Helmand last night. Beautifully decorated and really great food. The baby pumpkin was to die for! We will definitely be back soon.

Delicious food but poor service  I ordered a mantwo, which was quite nice, and my companions who tried various kabobs also appeared to be pleased by their entrees. The restaurant seems to be frequented by quite a few customers, however, the servers do not seem to be very motivated to serve. Every customer that I observed spent around 10-20 minutes to be seated around the entrance. Tables are neither occupied nor reserved, customers just had to wait till the servers could arrange the situation and greet them. I also felt a bit rushed to 'order, eat and go' as soon as possible. I think this renders the overall experience a dinner at an overpriced fast-food restaurant with exotic food.
Excellent food, excellent service every time! My favorite Baltimore restaurant.
Among Baltimore's best.
Delicious food and decent decoration. The staff are very friendly and attentive to there customers. Highly recommended.
Delicious and just elegant enough for a date!

Beautiful atmosphere and very high quality food. The lime cilantro sauce (I think that is what is in it?) is incredible and the pumpkin appatizer with the garlic yogurt is also phenomenal. From my two visits service is hit or miss but definitely not bad regardless. Could use some nice ambiance music. Overall a great dinner and I certainly will return again.

Good food but maybe not what I would expect for the price. The restaurant space is a little cramped but it's almost always busy, so maybe that's just my perception. Lot's of good vegetarian options (I'm not a vegetarian so I can't comment of the quality), and the staff is attentive. A good experience overall, but the cramped dining room was a challenge for me.
Maybe the best restaurant in the city? Never had even close to a bad experience here. It's been the same since I first went in 2008.
The waitress was so nice. She took the time to explain everything to us. The food was really delicious. So happy I went. Will definitely go back again.

Very delicious food, friendly and attentive staff and nice ombiance. My first time there with a group of friends; had the family style four course meal and got to sample the whole menu. I will definitely be back.
Nice restaurant with good food. I feel the price can be little low, however, good staff with delicious food.

Great lamb, great cocktails. Don't understand reviews that complain about the service. The people are nice and we've never had a problem. Minus one star for acoustics which bring out my inner grumpy grandpa, bc when really crowded it can be nearly impossible to hear your dining companions. Food makes up for it though
Good food, nice atmosphere and reasonably priced
Excellent food  especially the vegetarian platter.

White table cloths, attentive but not fussy service, all foods ordered by us  three at the table looked, smelled, tasted delightfully, portions were deluxe, and everything -including the wine- were fairly priced.  Go here.
Good food atmosphere and staff.
Great food. Great service. Get a good variety of everything it is all good. Do the family style special if possible.
Do not second guess eating here.  It's awesome and perfect everytime I come here to eat.   Total 5 star!
Very enjoyable evening. Great Food!

The food at The Helmand was delicious and was only matched by the service that was provided by the waitstaff. The dishes were reasonably priced (most things were in the high $10s-low $20 range), but we were made to feel like we were dining at a much more expensive establishment.
Decent Afghan food. It is a little too Americanized for me, but if you want to try the cuisine, it is a good place to dabble.
Without a doubt a baltimore treasure! You should hit it up if you're in town!!!

A friend hosted a celebration dinner, and we ate family-style, a raft of appetizers followed by plates of (what must be) the best of the house. It may be among the best "Middle Eastern" food I have ever had. Lamb with cinnamon carrots over rice; chicken kebab with a salad; salmon with spinach and pilau; spicy meatballs; a stewed chicken with vegetables. All were excellent, some were eye-opening wonders. ("I've entered Paradise!" said my wife on tasting the chicken kebab.) The appetizers were great, too, but there's no way I could identify or list them. Go. Be fed and amazed.
I like to bring guests here from out of town. The food's great and the location can't be beat.

I have been coming to Helmand over the past 14 years and been at their Boston restaurant as well. The food is honest and without pretensions. This is a must go whenever I am in Baltimore or in Boston. The Chowpan which is a lightly seasoned rack of lamb is a must try.

I have been to the Helmand three times in four years. Each time the food has been 'okay' not spectacular, but it has been nice to explore parts of the Afghan cuisine.  This last time I sensed a difference.  The chicken skewer and meatballs were adequate (somewhat spiced, but not delicious).  But the real difference was in service.  The restaurant had a good number of clientele but the waiters (servers) just didn't really care.  I asked for 'no rice' and then got rice -- and then a small plate was returned to me- ('no rice') with basically nothing on it at all.  And the service interactions were almost rude-- as if the staff was saying  'we have so many customers why should we care about you '.  Know that I will not be returning again.  There are many other lovely restaurants in Baltimore.
DELICIOUS!!! Excellent service.
Food and Service was great.
Amazing food and delightful service. Highly recommend!
Good afghan dinner you can go with your office colleagues for quick dinner

Overall excellent experience. The food was great, there were plenty of vegetarian options, all with amazing but not overpowering flavors. The restaurant was packed, and the tables very closer together than what I'm normally used to, but it was well worth it.  Make sure to have a reservation though.
Amazing Afghani food. Great for a date or a celebration. Start with the pumpkin appetizer and save room for the special ice cream.

Appetizers were mediocre. Also they charge you for bread??! If you're looking for the salad/white sauce experience this is not for you. They're definitely trying to go for something fancier. Also, don't get the mantu. It's mostly onions and potatoes with a tiny amount of meat. Almost everyone I know makes it better.  However, the chicken kabob was amazing. Super juicy, fresh, tender, not dry at all. It might be one of the best chicken kabob dishes I've ever had. The lamb seekh kabob isn't halal so I couldn't try it.
Some of the best food out there! Always have a great meal.
Loved the food. Service was pleasant.
Very nice atmosphere and professional service. Absolutely delicious food. Some of the best food I've had in Baltimore, maybe anywhere.
Excellent Afghan food
Great service, lovely setting, well priced. Had the lamb and beef meat balls which were cooked to perfection - though the sauce was a v v v tad sweet for my liking. A sound dinner destination.
very good food. ...tasty,  right amount of spices. ...clean tables,  table cloth.....it was fully packed on a Sunday evening

I have been to the Helmand three times and had three wonderful meals. The service is fast and friendly. The food is delicious. The flavors are surprising and delightful. I cannot recommend this restaurant highly enough. The only dish that I have ordered multiple times is the Kaddo Borwani, which is an excellent pumpkin based appetizer. My wife is a vegetarian and has enjoyed the wide variety  of options available on the menu.

The Helmand has been an outstanding restaurant in the Mount Vernon neighborhood for several decades. Superior Afghanistan food excellent  ( and reasonable Wine by the bottle), great service, beautiful dining experience. Come & treat yourself at one of the best restaurants in Baltimore
Food and service were excellent. Awesome experience.
Fab food! great service
Best Afghan food, i have had. The place is crowded.

This was my first visit to the Helmand and I was extremely excited to go because of all the wonderful statements friends and colleagues have made. Initially, the experience was great, the food was amazing, and the wine selection was decent. …
Great food!

I have tried this place twice now, once at the restaurant and delivery for the second time. The preparations are unique and amazing. The food bears a great deal of resemblance with Indian/Pakistani cuisine.

Food is prepared beforehand and doesn't seem to be made to order. The salmon dish came out cold and includes  reheated frozen vegetables. The service was good, but I was pretty disappointed with the food quality after what I've heard.
Another perfect meal. Great service and food that transports your soul. Already looking forward to my next visit.
Excellent food and huge portions! I loved the theme and the decorations as well as the overall presentation. It was so nice to find somewhere not as mainstream.
